{
  "texts": [
    "In the case \"miRNA + clinical\" of TCGA-BRCA dataset, Surv-OmiVAE outperformed AUTOSurv (median C-index 0.756 vs 0.738, p-value = 0.027).",
    "When multi-omics data were considered, however, AUTOSurv was able to beat Surv-OmiVAE (TCGA-BRCA: median C-index 0.749 vs 0.740, p-value = 0.027; TCGA-OV: median C-index 0.629 vs 0.601, p-value = 0.020).",
    "Furthermore, Surv-OmiVAE did not gain improvement in performance from multi-omics input features compared to single omics.",
    "Overall, our findings suggest that \"task-oriented feature extraction\" can potentially help capture survival-related information in the latent features and hence increase the prediction accuracy of LFSurv.",
    "Nevertheless, further adaptations are needed to accommodate multi-omics scenarios and make full use of information from different omics types."
  ]
}